## ISSUE 14: Soma Smashes a Standing Stone — No Follow-Up

**Location:** Scenes (Battle at the Circle of Thunder)

**Issue:** One bullet point in the Battle scene states: "Soma, in her elk form, smashes one of the standing stones of the henge." This action — destroying part of an ancient magical henge during a live ritual — has no follow-up, consequence, or acknowledgment anywhere else in the recap.

**Evidence:** The party document describes the Circle of Thunder as "a henge of ancient standing stones crackling with dark energy." Destroying a standing stone during a summoning ritual would plausibly have narrative or mechanical consequences. The recap's aftermath section describes the storm dissipating and the stones going "utterly inert," but makes no reference to one of them being physically destroyed.

**Suggested Fix:** Either remove the detail about Soma destroying a standing stone if it did not occur, or add a note in the Aftermath section acknowledging the physical damage to the henge and flagging whether this has any significance for the site going forward.

